<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/79912732-miriam-copeland"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/79912732-miriam-copeland">Miriam Copeland</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Well, the series is set in an alternate/parallel universe where the Crimean War is still going on, but in our universe, at the time this book is set, <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Well, the series is set in an alternate/parallel universe where the Crimean War is still going on, but in our universe, at the time this book is set, the Crimean war would have been long over with. (October 1853 to February 1856)<br />In short, yes. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
